    "This function provides a measure of the value of an action taken in a specific state, offering insight into the desirability of that action under the current policy [29].There are two types of policy learning methods, namely on-policy and offpolicy.",
    "In on-policy learning, agent tries to learn a policy that is close to the exploration strategy-i.e., the learned policy is influenced by the exploration strategy.",
    "While, in off-policy learning, the learned policy is independent of the exploration strategy, i.e., exploration during the learning phase is not based on the learned policy.",
    "Q-learning, a prominent example of off-policy learning, refines the target policy Ã by utilizing samples obtained from a distinct stochastic behavior policy within the environment.",
    "This approach allows Q-learning to learn the optimal policy even while exploring the environment using a different policy."
  ],
